definition.value: The dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups of citraconic acid.
A tertiary amine oxide resulting from the oxidation of the pyrrolidine nitrogen of nicotine.
Ferrocene substituted on one of the cyclopentadienyl rings by an ethyl group.
A  diether that is ethylene glycol in which the hydrogens of the hydroxy groups have been replaced by 2-[bis(carboxymethyl)amino]ethyl group respectively.
A 1,2-glycol compound produced via reaction of ethylene oxide with water.
An oxodicarboxylic acid that is succinic acid bearing a single oxo group.
A monocarboxylic acid that is toluene in which one of the hydrogens of the methyl group has been replaced by a carboxy group.
A compound comprising a benzene ring core carrying a carboxylic acid substituent.
A monochlorobenzoic acid carrying a chloro substituent at position 4.
A chlorobenzoic acid that is benzoic acid in which the ring hydrogens at positions 2 and 4 are substituted by chloro groups.
A monocarboxylic acid that is acetic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by a 4-chlorophenyl group.
